                            <comment id="13431" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2005 07:42:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The jar file generation code in the Maven script is dated. I&apos;ve removed it completely, as the Maven build is not intended to be fully featured in the first place.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The stuff in the Ant build is the reference here. It does include the JNDI support in a module jar file: not in &quot;spring-jdbc.jar&quot; but rather in &quot;spring-context.jar&quot;. Spring&apos;s JNDI lookup support should only be relevant in a Spring application context, that&apos;s why they reside in the context jar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
